From this day and after that. Show you're standing [up]. Come from your offices, your homes, your schools and universities. Come in the name of peace. Come with Ukrainian symbols, to support Ukraine, to support freedom, to support life.

Come to your squares, your streets...make yourselves visible and heard. Say that people matter, freedom matters, peace matters, Ukraine matters. From March 24th, in downtowns of your cities, all as one--together--who want to stop the war.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/I5oz6pE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[oldbaldjewishman]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I meant to do that</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/E5gnjIF</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Enb2Avy.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/E5gnjIF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[funkystay]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>6 weeks of science and sailing, best day right here!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/vkuZWaX</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/14a6rbk.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We caught a Portuguese man o' war on one of our science stations!
They are a jelly with basically a sail on top!
We collected a metric ton of sargassum (floating planty bit in lower right is a fragment of some) for the various research projects of the students and visiting scientist, thats where the crabs and stuff came from</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/59lV6lS.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>They flip/roll to get both sides of their "sail" wet and keep themselves from drying out
We had an amazing day where we saw over a hundred of these guys floating past us per hour, for several hours!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/S7uuVVw.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I spent a good chunk of time with this dude because he was so neat! Pearly tentacles and the stringy light purple ones, and the chunky spiral dark purple and white ones, all seem to be for different uses.
Note: I'm a ships engineer not a scientist, so purely non-scientific facts here!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3198lij.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He seemed to like keeping his security blankie (the orange spray can cap) close but we took it away before sending him back on his way in the ocean, sorry buddy, but you don't need the plastic!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8XCrX9C.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tiny paintings for all the students on final exams/paper/presentation/projects week!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9ZL9t2y.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And some for the crew cause they worked hard too!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/90cTW3G.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sunset at sea while hove-to under sail for a science deployment station
Arrived at anchor just off Key West, FL today after meandering through most all of the Caribbean islands on the SSV (Sailing School Vessel) Corwith Cramer doing science and sail training with university students</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/vkuZWaX</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[readingrabbit]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Please slap these repressive but-nuggets down every time they pop up! Good job Gov. Cox!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gB5bXvJ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4YaZsZ6.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gB5bXvJ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[dickblack12]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Check your registration now.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/sJao63R</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ValEOFv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/sJao63R</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WHEREISMYTROPHY]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Such patience!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NgAbLrT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/efY6CD4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#strong #supremecourt</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NgAbLrT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[brunner73]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>u wot mate ?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/t2SvtcI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/coWXyTP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/t2SvtcI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[piconuke]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Crowd stays silent so Jules Hoogland, who is blind, can hear where to throw. She definitely heard the cheers.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SXfy5OH<